curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/821' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM2038", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM2038 is a low noise, low dropout voltage  linear regulator which is designed using CMOS  technology. It provides 500mA output current capability.  The operating input voltage range is from 0.8V to 5.5V  and bias supply voltage range is from 2.5V to 5.5V. The  output voltage range is from 0.8V to 3.6V.  Other features include logic-controlled shutdown mode,  short-circuit current limit and thermal shutdown  protection. The SGM2038 has automatic discharge  function to quickly discharge VOUT in the disabled status.  The SGM2038 is suitable for applications which need  low noise, fast transient response and low IQ  consumption, such as battery-powered equipment and  smartphones, etc.  The SGM2038 is available in a Green UTDFN-1.2×1.2-4L  package. It operates over an operating temperature  range of -40℃ to +125℃.    "}'
